A tool to collect DNS records passively to aid Incident handling, Network Security Monitoring
and general digital forensics.

PassiveDNS sniffes the interface or reads a pcap-file and outputs the DNS-server answers.
Example output from version 0.1.1:

# timestamp||sniffing-host|dns-server-IP||<The answer from the DNS server>
1304063713||localhost||8.8.8.8||QUERY,NOERROR,31882,qr|rd|ra||1||gamelinux.org,IN,A||1||gamelinux.org,IN,A,361,85.19.221.54||0||0
1304063713||localhost||8.8.8.8||QUERY,NOERROR,45422,qr|rd|ra||1||gamelinux.org,IN,AAAA||0||1||gamelinux.org,IN,SOA,1800,ns.netimage.no,hostmaster.netimage.no,2010102501,3600,3600,3024000,86400||0
1304063713||localhost||8.8.8.8||QUERY,NOERROR,13533,qr|rd|ra||1||gamelinux.org,IN,MX||1||gamelinux.org,IN,MX,361,1,mail.gamelinux.org||0||0



